  "original_title": "\u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1 \u0db1\u0dd0\u0dc0\u0dca \u0d91\u0db1 \u0daf\u0dd2\u0db1 \u0d9c\u0dd0\u0db1 \u0d87\u0db8\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Minister tells about the date of arrival of fuel ships",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mr. Kanchana Wijesekera, Minister of Electricity and Energy, has announced on his Twitter account the dates of the arrival of the diesel and petrol ships that have paid cash and advance payments.",
        "Accordingly, the Central Bank and the Ministry of Finance jointly paid the I.O.C. owned by the company",
        "A petrol ship is scheduled to arrive in Sri Lanka on the 22nd-24th.",
        "A petrol ship is also scheduled to arrive in Lanka between 17-19.",
        "The Minister says that a Borale ship is scheduled to arrive in Sri Lanka between 15-17.",
        "The minister further said that the ship which was supposed to arrive on the 9th could not arrive due to bad weather and the supplier has informed that the ship has already left India."
      ],
